@prefix : <#> .
@prefix schema: <http://schema.org/> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix onto: <../ontology.ttl#> .
@prefix prov: <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#> .

: a schema:CreativeWork ;
    schema:name "Server-Side Delegation INSERT Gate"@en ;
    schema:description "Gate procedure for registering oplcert:hasIdentityDelegate on a delegator's profile graph via SPARQL INSERT with the delegate's public key inline."@en ;
    schema:dateCreated "2026-06-28T18:35:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:dateModified "2026-06-30T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:author <https://linkedin.com/in/kidehen#this> ;
    schema:about :delegationInsertHowTo .

:delegationInsertHowTo a schema:HowTo ;
    schema:name "Server-Side Delegation INSERT Procedure"@en ;
    schema:description "Steps for correctly registering a delegation relationship on a delegator's Virtuoso profile graph via SPARQL INSERT, including mandatory public key data."@en ;
    schema:step :step-studyExistingPattern, :step-insertWithPublicKey, :step-askVerification, :step-profileVerification .

:step-studyExistingPattern a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 1 ;
    schema:name "Study existing delegator profile for triple shape"@en ;
    schema:text "Before writing the INSERT, fetch a known delegator profile that already has hasIdentityDelegate (e.g., curl -sL -H 'Accept: text/turtle' 'https://my.openlinksw.com/dataspace/person/kidehen@openlinksw.com') and grep for hasIdentityDelegate + cert:key. Confirm the delegate's public key is stored inline as a blank node with cert:modulus and cert:exponent. This establishes the triple shape to replicate."@en .

:step-insertWithPublicKey a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 2 ;
    schema:name "SPARQL INSERT with delegate public key inline"@en ;
    schema:text """Execute this INSERT DATA against the delegator's SPARQL endpoint (using Digest auth for the ODS user), substituting the delegator and delegate WebIDs and the delegate's cert:modulus and cert:exponent:

SPARQL
PREFIX cert: <http://www.w3.org/ns/auth/cert#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX oplcert: <http://www.openlinksw.com/schemas/cert#>

INSERT DATA {
  GRAPH <{DELEGATOR_WEBID}> {
    <{DELEGATOR_WEBID}>
      oplcert:hasIdentityDelegate
      <{DELEGATE_WEBID}> .

    <{DELEGATE_WEBID}>
      cert:key [
        cert:modulus "{MODULUS}"^^xsd:hexBinary ;
        cert:exponent "{EXPONENT}"^^xsd:int
      ]
  }
}
;

The modulus is extracted from the delegate's PKCS#12 cert via:
  openssl pkcs12 -in cert.p12 -passin pass:$PW -nokeys -clcerts | openssl x509 -noout -modulus

The exponent is always 65537 (0x10001) for RSA 2048 keys. The delegate's modulus and exponent must match what is in the delegate's own WebID profile document for the cert:key blank node; otherwise the WebID-TLS verification chain breaks.

Repeat for each delegator WebID that needs the reciprocal delegation relationship."""@en .

:step-askVerification a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 3 ;
    schema:name "Verify via SPARQL ASK"@en ;
    schema:text """After executing the INSERT, verify the triple was stored in the target graph using SPARQL ASK:

SPARQL
PREFIX oplcert: <http://www.openlinksw.com/schemas/cert#>

ASK
FROM <{DELEGATOR_WEBID}>
WHERE {
  <{DELEGATOR_WEBID}>
    oplcert:hasIdentityDelegate
    <{DELEGATE_WEBID}>
}
;

A true response confirms the triple exists in the specified graph. A false response means it was not stored — check Digest auth credentials, graph IRI spelling, and endpoint permissions."""@en .

:step-profileVerification a schema:HowToStep ;
    schema:position 4 ;
    schema:name "Verify via profile content negotiation"@en ;
    schema:text """Re-fetch the delegator's Turtle profile via content negotiation to confirm ODS serves the new triple:

  curl -sL -H 'Accept: text/turtle' '{DELEGATOR_WEBID}' | grep hasIdentityDelegate

If the ASK returned true but the triple is absent from the Turtle profile, ODS may source its profile Turtle from a different graph — investigate with:

SPARQL
SELECT ?g WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g { <{DELEGATOR_WEBID}> oplcert:hasIdentityDelegate ?any }
}

Then update the INSERT's GRAPH clause to target the correct graph and re-execute. Optionally run On-Behalf-Of verification against a WebID verification service to end-to-end test the delegation chain."""@en .
